# Documentation — Dummy section first

Seth's brain connects easier with simplicity. When creating or editing documentation under `docs/`, **always include a Dummy section** at the top.

## Required structure

```markdown
# Title

## Dummy section (start here)

[Plain analogy + simple diagram + Orchi mapping]

---

[Technical content]
```

## Rules

- Dummy section goes **immediately after the title**, before any other section
- Use everyday analogies (pizza layers, mail forwarding, etc.) — not abstract pattern names alone
- Include a visual (ASCII diagram or small table) and a one-sentence "aha"
- Map analogy → Orchi in a short table or bullet list
- End Dummy with a signpost: technical detail follows below
- Keep Dummy short; put depth in sections after `---`

## Reference

Follow `docs/patterns/decorator.md` and the `orchi-documentation` skill (`.cursor/skills/orchi-documentation/SKILL.md`).
